\
No single development in Week 12 transformed the system. The clock\'92s face did not jump. Instead, the week deepened an existing pattern: emergency powers used as normal tools, law bent toward friends and against foes, universities and agencies steered by threat and reward, and the informational ground under citizens\'92 feet made less stable. Resistance appeared\'97in courtrooms, on campuses, in the streets\'97but it was reactive, often confined to individual cases or narrow domains. The structure of power continued to tilt toward a presidency that governs by decree, backed by a security and information apparatus increasingly aligned with its interests.\
\
